caption.p: Factor H and VCP inhibit transduction of MDCK cells by H1N1-pseudotyped lentiviral particles. Western blotting to show expression of hemagglutinin (HA) in purified H1N1 and H3N2 pseudotyped lentiviral particles (A). HA expression was evident at ~70 kDa. Luciferase reporter activity of H1N1 and H3N2 pseudotyped lentiviral particles-transduced cells with factor H and VCP (B). Significance was determined using the unpaired one-way ANOVA test (** p < 0.01 and *** p < 0.001) ( n = 3).
